# Contributing

The canonical working conventions live in [`AGENTS.md`](AGENTS.md) and the
[Repo Standard](REPO-STANDARD.md). Start there. This file is a thin human entry
point and does not duplicate those rules.

## Orientation

- **What goes where** — [`REPO-STANDARD.md`](REPO-STANDARD.md) and [docs/README.md](docs/README.md).
- **Principles & quality gates** — [`CONSTITUTION.md`](CONSTITUTION.md).
- **Build, test, boundaries** — [`AGENTS.md`](AGENTS.md).

## Before opening a PR

- Run the repo's verification gate (see `AGENTS.md` / the constitution).
- Capture durable cross-cutting decisions as an ADR in `docs/decisions/adrs/`.
- Commits: plain bodies, no `Co-Authored-By` trailer.
